title: Calculate the Angular Speed in $$\frac{rad}{s}$$
text: What is $$w=\frac{v}{r}$$ in $$\frac{rad}{s}$$ after substituting $$v=\frac{60m}{s}$$, $$r=\frac{0.85m}{2}$$? (round to nearst integer)

title: Unit Conversion
text: Since $$1$$ revolution is equal to $$2\pi$$ radians and $$1$$ minute is $$60$$ seconds, $$\frac{rev}{min}=$$ $$\frac{60\frac{rad}{s}}{2} \pi$$. Now convert $$141$$ $$\frac{rad}{s}$$ to $$\frac{rev}{min}$$.
